            "block_button": "Learn more",
            "popup_content": "<h5> Ainsley Erzen | Soccer &amp; Track </h5>\n<h6> University of Arkansas Dual-Sport Athlete | NCAA 4x800 Record-Holder </h6>\n\n<p> Told she couldn’t compete in both soccer and track? Ainsley Erzen did it anyway. As a junior, Erzen and her 4x800 relay teammates broke the collegiate two-mile relay record in March 2025. She also took a stand for female athletes by writing in the Des Moines Register and joining Iowa Gov. Kim Reynolds as she signed a law protecting women’s sports in Iowa.  </p>\n\n<p> Instagram:<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/ainsley_erzen\"> @ainsley_erzen </a></p>",
